     "text": [
      "## Purpose\n",
      "This runbook describes the operational procedures to deploy, upgrade, roll back, and safely disable the **perf-canary** service across regions.\n",
      "\n",
      "perf-canary is a lightweight, always-on synthetic workload that calls internal inference endpoints for a curated model set and emits performance metrics (p50/p95/p99, tokens/sec, prefill/decode, queueing time, batch stats). The service must stay under the defined overhead budget and must not capture or emit customer data.\n",
      "\n",
      "**Primary users:** Eng-Infra on-call and Release Engineering during rollouts.\n",
      "\n",
      "---\n",
      "\n",
      "## Quick reference\n",
      "**Service name:** perf-canary\n",
      "\n",
      "**Deployment mechanism:**\n",
      "- Terraform: service account / IAM / secrets / region wiring\n",
      "- Helm: workload deployment and per-region config\n",
      "\n",
      "**Primary dashboards:**\n",
      "- Grafana: \"Perf Canary – Per Model\" (p95, tokens/sec, breakdowns)\n",
      "- Capacity/overhead: GPU utilization + canary QPS counters\n",
      "\n",
      "**Kill switch:** control-plane config (disable flag) + Helm scale-to-zero (last resort)\n",
      "\n",
      "**Slack channels:**\n",
      "- #eng-runtime (warnings / runtime attribution)\n",
      "- #eng-oncall (paging / incident coordination)\n",
      "- #eng-releases (rollout sequencing)\n",
      "\n",
      "**Owners:**\n",
      "- Infra/rollout coordination: Vanessa Ortiz\n",
      "- Runtime canary TL: Noah Patel\n",
      "- SRE readiness: Sean Gallagher / Rafael Mendes\n",
      "\n",
      "---\n",
      "\n",
      "## Safety and guardrails (must-read)\n",
      "1) **Overhead budget:** perf-canary must remain below the region budget (target <0.5% of GPU capacity for covered models). If overhead is uncertain, do not expand coverage.\n",
      "2) **No customer data:** only synthetic prompts. perf-canary must not log prompts, user identifiers, request ids from customer traffic, or raw outputs.\n",
      "3) **Least privilege:** perf-canary uses a restricted service account with inference read access and metrics write access only.\n",
      "4) **Cardinality control:** metrics must not include high-cardinality labels (prompt id, request id, full model string variants). Use canonical model/version identifiers.\n",
      "\n",
      "If any of the above is violated or suspected, **disable perf-canary immediately** (see “Safe-disable procedures”).\n",
      "\n",
      "---\n",
      "\n",
      "## Preconditions\n",
      "Before deploying or upgrading perf-canary in a region, confirm:\n",
      "- You have the correct change window and announcement in #eng-releases (or an approved emergency change).\n",
      "- The control-plane canary config for the target region has been reviewed/validated (model allowlist and thresholds).\n",
      "- Telemetry pipeline is healthy (no known ingestion lag that would delay alerts).\n",
      "- Dashboards exist for the region and links in alert payloads resolve.\n",
      "- Warning alerts are enabled first; paging is enabled only after calibration and sign-off.\n",
      "\n",
      "Required access:\n",
      "- Kubernetes deploy permissions for the region’s perf-canary namespace\n",
      "- Terraform apply permissions for the relevant env (prod)\n",
      "- Ability to view Grafana, logs, and alert routing configuration\n",
      "\n",
      "---\n",
      "\n",
      "## Deployment topology (conceptual)\n",
      "perf-canary runs as a small Deployment in each region:\n",
      "- Calls internal inference endpoints via restricted auth scope\n",
      "- Uses a seedable synthetic prompt-shape generator\n",
      "- Emits metrics to the standard metrics pipeline (histograms + counters)\n",
      "- Fetches baseline artifacts / config from baseline store and control-plane config\n",
      "\n",
      "Key runtime attribution tags expected in metrics:\n",
      "- runtime_build_id\n",
      "- kernel_selection_id (or kernel version tag)\n",
      "- model_id + model_version\n",
      "- hardware_sku\n",
      "- region\n",
      "\n",
      "---\n",
      "\n",
      "## Standard rollout sequence\n",
      "Use this sequence for net-new region enablement or for major upgrades:\n",
      "1) Deploy/upgrade **with alerts disabled** (metrics only)\n",
      "2) Validate metrics emission and overhead\n",
      "3) Enable **warning** alerts\n",
      "4) Run 3–7 days; tune thresholds if needed\n",
      "5) Enable **paging** only after SRE/runtime sign-off for top models\n",
      "\n",
      "Avoid simultaneous risky changes:\n",
      "- Do not expand model coverage and change runtime version in the same window.\n",
      "- Do not enable paging on the same day you add a new region.\n",
      "\n",
      "---\n",
      "\n",
      "## Procedure A — New region enablement (first-time)\n",
      "### A1. Confirm regional prerequisites\n",
      "- Verify the region has:\n",
      "  - inference endpoints reachable from perf-canary namespace\n",
      "  - required secrets provisioned (auth scope token material)\n",
      "  - dashboards pre-created or templated panels available\n",
      "\n",
      "### A2. Terraform apply (IAM + secrets wiring)\n",
      "1) Pull latest main in the infra repo.\n",
      "2) Confirm the perf-canary service account exists and is scoped correctly.\n",
      "3) Apply the region module changes.\n",
      "\n",
      "Expected outcomes:\n",
      "- Service account is created/updated\n",
      "- Secrets are provisioned/rotated as needed\n",
      "- Network policies allow egress to inference endpoints and metrics ingestion\n",
      "\n",
      "### A3. Helm install (metrics-only)\n",
      "1) Install the perf-canary chart into the region namespace with:\n",
      "   - conservative QPS caps\n",
      "   - limited model list (2–3 models)\n",
      "   - warnings/paging disabled (or alert rules muted)\n",
      "2) Wait for the Deployment to become Ready.\n",
      "\n",
      "### A4. Validate\n",
      "Within 30 minutes, confirm:\n",
      "- perf-canary pods are stable (no crash loops)\n",
      "- Metrics appear in Grafana:\n",
      "  - latency histograms for e2e and runtime-only\n",
      "  - tokens/sec counters\n",
      "  - queueing time if enabled\n",
      "- Labels are correct and low-cardinality.\n",
      "- Overhead remains within budget.\n",
      "\n",
      "### A5. Enable warning alerts\n",
      "- Unmute/enable warning rules for the region and model set.\n",
      "- Confirm incident-bot threads route to #eng-runtime (not paging).\n",
      "\n",
      "### A6. Post-enable monitoring checklist\n",
      "For the next 24 hours:\n",
      "- Watch for noisy alerts (flapping) and ingestion lag.\n",
      "- Confirm baseline lookups are succeeding (no “baseline missing” warnings).\n",
      "\n",
      "---\n",
      "\n",
      "## Procedure B — Standard upgrade (same region)\n",
      "Examples: perf-canary image bump, config schema update, or dependency update.\n",
      "\n",
      "### B1. Pre-flight\n",
      "- Identify what is changing:\n",
      "  - Image tag only vs chart changes vs config changes\n",
      "- Check if the change affects:\n",
      "  - metrics schema/labels\n",
      "  - baseline fetch logic\n",
      "  - QPS / overhead\n",
      "- Announce upgrade start time in #eng-releases if it could affect alerting noise.\n",
      "\n",
      "### B2. Upgrade via Helm\n",
      "1) Confirm current version:\n",
      "   - helm list / helm history (region)\n",
      "2) Apply upgrade:\n",
      "   - helm upgrade with the new image tag/chart version\n",
      "3) Watch rollout:\n",
      "   - ensure pods drain/replace cleanly\n",
      "\n",
      "### B3. Validate after upgrade\n",
      "- Confirm metrics continuity:\n",
      "  - no gaps beyond expected rollout window\n",
      "  - histogram buckets unchanged unless explicitly approved\n",
      "- Confirm alert payload links still point to correct dashboards/runbooks.\n",
      "- Confirm overhead hasn’t increased.\n",
      "\n",
      "### B4. Roll forward / stop criteria\n",
      "If any of the following occurs, stop further upgrades and consider rollback:\n",
      "- sustained error rate calling inference endpoints\n",
      "- missing baseline artifacts causing continuous alert noise\n",
      "- overhead increase >20% relative to prior canary overhead in the same region\n",
      "- new high-cardinality labels introduced (metrics volume spike)\n",
      "\n",
      "---\n",
      "\n",
      "## Procedure C — Rollback (Helm)\n",
      "Use when a perf-canary deploy/upgrade causes instability, overhead spikes, metrics breakage, or alert storms attributable to canary itself.\n",
      "\n",
      "### C1. Decide rollback vs disable\n",
      "- If perf-canary is **functioning but noisy**: prefer to mute alerts / adjust config, not rollback.\n",
      "- If perf-canary is **malfunctioning** (crash loop, spamming endpoints, violating safety constraints): rollback immediately.\n",
      "- If safety/privacy is at risk: disable immediately (see “Safe-disable procedures”), then rollback.\n",
      "\n",
      "### C2. Execute rollback\n",
      "1) Identify last known good revision:\n",
      "   - helm history perf-canary\n",
      "2) Roll back:\n",
      "   - helm rollback perf-canary <REVISION>\n",
      "3) Watch:\n",
      "   - pods become Ready\n",
      "   - error logs subside\n",
      "   - metrics return to expected shape\n",
      "\n",
      "### C3. Post-rollback tasks\n",
      "- Confirm alert rules are in the desired state (muted/unmuted).\n",
      "- Update #eng-releases and #eng-runtime with:\n",
      "  - what was rolled back\n",
      "  - why\n",
      "  - whether model coverage or alerting was impacted\n",
      "- File follow-up ticket referencing rollback revision and observed symptoms.\n",
      "\n",
      "---\n",
      "\n",
      "## Procedure D — Safe-disable procedures (kill switch)\n",
      "Use to stop canary load quickly without impacting inference endpoints.\n",
      "\n",
      "### D1. Preferred: disable via control-plane config\n",
      "This is the safest path because it preserves Deployment health while stopping workload generation.\n",
      "1) Set region enablement to disabled for perf-canary (control-plane flag).\n",
      "2) Confirm perf-canary acknowledges config refresh (logs/metric indicating “targets=0” or “disabled=true”).\n",
      "3) Verify:\n",
      "   - QPS to inference endpoints drops to ~0\n",
      "   - metrics stop changing except for heartbeat/health\n",
      "\n",
      "### D2. Secondary: set model list empty / QPS cap to zero\n",
      "If full disable is not available but config is reachable:\n",
      "- Set canary target models to an empty allowlist for that region OR set QPS cap to 0.\n",
      "- Validate the request loop stops.\n",
      "\n",
      "### D3. Last resort: scale Deployment to zero\n",
      "Use only if config plane is unavailable or the service is misbehaving.\n",
      "1) kubectl scale deployment/perf-canary --replicas=0\n",
      "2) Confirm traffic stops (endpoint QPS counters drop).\n",
      "3) Leave a note in the incident thread explaining why last resort was required.\n",
      "\n",
      "### D4. After disabling\n",
      "- If this was due to privacy/safety concerns: open a Sev2 incident (minimum) and notify Security & Compliance.\n",
      "- If due to overhead: capture before/after GPU utilization and canary QPS for later tuning.\n",
      "\n",
      "---\n",
      "\n",
      "## Verification checklist (what “good” looks like)\n",
      "### Health\n",
      "- Pods Running/Ready; restarts stable\n",
      "- No sustained inference call errors\n",
      "\n",
      "### Metrics\n",
      "- E2E latency histogram present\n",
      "- Runtime-only latency histogram present (if instrumented)\n",
      "- tokens/sec present\n",
      "- Queueing time present (if enabled in runtime)\n",
      "- kernel/runtime/model version tags present\n",
      "\n",
      "### Cardinality\n",
      "- Labels limited to: model_id, model_version, region, hardware_sku, runtime_build_id, kernel_selection_id, tier (optional)\n",
      "- No prompt_id, request_id, pod_uid labels\n",
      "\n",
      "### Overhead\n",
      "- Canary QPS respects configured caps\n",
      "- Estimated GPU overhead within regional budget\n",
      "\n",
      "---\n",
      "\n",
      "## Common failure modes and mitigations\n",
      "1) **Baseline missing / baseline fetch failing**\n",
      "   - Symptom: alerts or logs indicate “no baseline” and the evaluator can’t compute regression.\n",
      "   - Mitigation: disable alerts for affected model/region; restore baseline store access; verify model_id/model_version match canonical registry identifiers.\n",
      "\n",
      "2) **Telemetry ingestion lag**\n",
      "   - Symptom: alerts fire late; dashboards show step-like delays.\n",
      "   - Mitigation: do not tune thresholds based on delayed data; coordinate with Telemetry (Logan Wright / Nadia Rahman) to resolve lag.\n",
      "\n",
      "3) **Cardinality explosion / metrics cost spike**\n",
      "   - Symptom: metrics backend cost/volume alerts; Grafana queries slow.\n",
      "   - Mitigation: disable offending metrics emission or rollback; remove high-cardinality labels; follow the metrics cardinality audit guidance.\n",
      "\n",
      "4) **Overhead too high**\n",
      "   - Symptom: GPU utilization rises; inference queueing increases correlated with canary.\n",
      "   - Mitigation: reduce QPS caps; reduce model coverage; reduce concurrency; consider region-specific schedules.\n",
      "\n",
      "5) **Alerts flapping**\n",
      "   - Symptom: warning/paging repeatedly triggers and resolves.\n",
      "   - Mitigation: increase min sample size; extend dampening window; ensure region/SKU-aware thresholds if variance differs.\n",
      "\n",
      "---\n",
      "\n",
      "## Escalation and communication\n",
      "- **If customer impact is suspected:** follow the on-call incident process; page SRE on-call and notify #eng-oncall.\n",
      "- **If regression is real (not canary artifact):** engage Serving Runtime owners; include runtime_build_id and kernel_selection_id in the handoff.\n",
      "- **If infra/fleet correlation is suspected:** engage Fleet/Infra; include hardware_sku, region, and recent fleet change ids.\n",
      "\n",
      "In any escalation, include:\n",
      "- Region\n",
      "- Model + model version\n",
      "- Observed vs baseline metrics (p95, tokens/sec)\n",
      "- Sample size + evaluation window\n",
      "- Runtime build id + kernel selection id\n",
      "- Dashboard links and recent deploy/rollout context\n",
      "\n",
      "---\n",
      "\n",
      "## Change management notes\n",
      "- Prefer weekday business hours for region expansion and for enabling paging.\n",
      "- Use phased rollout: one region, limited models, warnings first.\n",
      "- Keep a clear revert path: last-known-good Helm revision and the disable switch confirmed.\n",
      "\n",
      "---\n",
      "\n",
      "## Appendix: Minimal rollback decision tree\n",
      "1) Is perf-canary violating safety/privacy constraints?\n",
      "   - Yes → Disable immediately (D1/D3), then rollback (C2).\n",
      "2) Is perf-canary generating excessive load/overhead?\n",
      "   - Yes → Disable (D1/D2). If still present → scale to zero (D3). Then tune and redeploy.\n",
      "3) Are alerts noisy due to thresholds/baseline drift?\n",
      "   - Yes → mute paging, adjust thresholds/min-samples/dampening; avoid rollback unless a code change caused it.\n",
      "4) Are metrics broken (missing tags/histograms) after upgrade?\n",
      "   - Yes → rollback to last known good; validate schema compatibility before retry.\n",
      "\n",
      "---\n",
      "\n",
      "## Revision history\n",
      "- 2025-12-18: Initial version for us-east phase-1 rollout.\n",
      "- 2026-02-14: Added control-plane disable path as preferred kill switch; expanded validation and overhead stop criteria.\n"
     ]
    }
